  <bioghist id="aspace_0a497331db1814eaf839a2f59733cbe6">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Walter H. Blucher was associated with the Detroit City Plan Commission, 1919-1934. He was Executive Director of the American Society of Planning Officials, 1934-1953, and of the Association of State Planning and Development Agencies, 1946-1953. Also, he was a member of the International Federation for Housing and Town Planning, the American Institute of Planners, Alpha Theta Kappa, and the Michigan Bar Association. Member, International Fraternity of Lambda Alpha, Ely Chapter.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_17244459bc389e7840778a8d46f1dd8d">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Includes planning files and reports; speeches; articles; monthly reports and minutes of the American Society of Planning Officials; minutes of the Association of State Planning and Development Agencies; annual reports of the Detroit City Plan Commission; pictures; and correspondence between Blucher and Rexford G. Tugwell.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_796823dc467c65fc7dd34ec285399aa3">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Walter Harold Blucher Papers, #3698. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
